Sales Grid of Offers for Channels
element.documentation: These are the actually grids use to price offerings for a give date and length of stay.

element.name: Sales Channel
element.documentation: This is the customer interaction point that the offer will be presented to the guest. We may sell or not sell at a specific or different price depending on sales channel.

element.name: Vendor
element.documentation: This is a company that fulfills orders for specific product/components.

element.name: Documentation
element.documentation: Receipts and/or documentation presented to guest as proof of a purchase,

element.name: Purchase Order (Work Order)
element.documentation: Request for a purchase of goods or services from a vendor as neccesary to complete a sales order. Often a wholesale transaction between companies for resale to a guest.

element.name: Transport Order
element.documentation:
Move Cargo from A - B
Export Documentation Hazardous Materials Document Tax and Tariff Document Airport Charges Document

element.name: Cargo
element.documentation: This is the freight that is being transported.

element.name: Party Account
element.documentation: Represents the contractual representative involved in a specific sales order. Given that fullfillment can occur later, parties sometimes have different agreement on when deposits are requrired and when complete payements are due.

element.name: Agent Partner
element.documentation: Respresents the legal entity that we are conduction business with, often with a specific agrement.

element.name: Agreement
element.documentation: Represents the relationship obligations the parties have agreed to. Could be custom pricing, tiered pricing, customer catalog or purchase rules like you cannot use a corporate card to buy a video game.

element.name: Partnership Agreement
element.documentation: Agreement to broker business between third parties, often with a commision based on the sale.

element.name: Shipper Agreement
element.documentation: Agreement to provide shipping services at a specific demand level and price

element.name: Services Agreement
element.documentation: Agreement to provide services at a specific demand level.

element.name: Pricing Agreement
element.documentation: Contract pricing for specific product, % off MSRP/RAW, etc.

element.name: Sales Order Adjustments
element.documentation: Could be returns or discounts applied to the sales order as it is immutable.

element.name: Shipment Order
element.documentation: Shipment of goods from point A to B by a carrier.

element.name: Route
element.documentation: This is the specific stops that cargo is transitioned through.

element.name: Packing Slip
element.documentation: Documentation of what is contained in a given shipment. For example, you order may have been shipped in two boxes, each of which would have a packing slip. Please note that this is not the same as a receipt, as packing slips often do not show pricing.

element.name: Bill of Lading
element.documentation: The Bill of Lading is a document of title of,goods, transferable by endorsement and is a receipt from shipping company regarding the number of packages with a particular weight and markings and a contract for the transportation of same to a port of destination mentioned therein.

element.name: Manifest
element.documentation: Manifest (transportation), a document listing the cargo, passengers, and crew of a ship, aircraft, or vehicle, for the use of customs and other officials

element.name: Offer Price & Availability
element.documentation: Represents our determination of offer availability, eligibility, and price we will show the profile as part of a shoppnig session.

element.name: Product Inventory Availability
element.documentation: Represent amount of inventory available for orders.

element.name: Warehouse Facility
element.documentation: Location which will complete the fulfillment of the assigned purchase order

element.name: Accounting Journal
element.documentation: Financial collection of all transaction between account journals.

element.name: General Ledger
element.documentation: The journal which records revenue.

element.name: Account
element.documentation: Represents the legal entity we are doing business with in the transaction, and/or over a period of time. Often contains the shipto, billto, payments, contacts and other information necessary for accounting.

element.name: Credential
element.documentation: Represent information or token used to identify a profile with a specific level of authentication. For example, we could only require a phone number to electronically store a receipt. However, an order history lookup may require a username and password. See Java Authentication and Authorization Service for more detail on the pattern.

element.name: Agent Profile
element.documentation: Represent the agent login information, preferences and other information necessary to complete an interaction.

element.name: Eligibility Rules
element.documentation: Define what, when and how much of a product can be purchased

element.name: Vendor Account
element.documentation: Represents a vendor account used to fulfill products associated with a sales order at an agreed up price and payment terms.

element.name: Shopping Session
element.documentation: Events, Offers Made during a party/agent/? shopping interaction. This is necessary to support security and orchestration of necessary shopping interations.

element.name: Shopping Basket
element.documentation: Represents the list of products or packages that the party or agent is collecting for a sales order. I.E. Presales
